msContents.summary: Book of prayers in Arabic, with some anecdotes about the life of the Prophet of Islam at the end in Turkish (p. 69-81).

textLang.#text: Arabic with 13 pages in Ottoman Turkish

supportDesc.extent: 41 paginated leaves : 170 x 110 (120 x 60) mm, bound to 170 x 110 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paginated in Hindu-Arabic numerals, upper outer corners; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Clear naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

binding.p: Brownish green leather over pasteboard with fore-edge flap. Gilt stamped with patterned double frame with gold tooled crosshatch and dots fill.

origin.p: Manuscript is undated, but likely produced sometime in the mid- to late-17th or 18th century. Possibly compiled and copied in Turkey.

history.provenance: Presumed to be a gift of David Eugene Smith, 1931-1934.
